==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Incogitancy
<hw>In*cog"i*tan*cy</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>incogitantia</ets>.]</ety> <def>Lack of thought, or of the power of
thinking; thoughtlessness; unreasonableness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>'T is folly and <qex>incogitancy</qex> to argue anything, one way
or the other, from the designs of a sort of beings with whom we so
little communicate.</q> <rj><qau>Glanvill.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Incogitant</ent>⟦br⟧
